  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Epigrammatist of the &#x2018;Garland&#x2019; of Meleager... (Anth. Pal. 4,1,28). Three poems are ascribed to him: 
      to &#x2018;M. from Samos&#x2019; (&#x39C;. &#x3A3;&#x3AC;&#x3BC;&#x3B9;&#x3BF;&#x3C2;) the epigrams Anth. Pal. 9,54 (= Stob. 4,50,62) and 55 (the alternative ascription to Lucillius could be correct),
      two distichs on old age, to &#x2018;M. from Smyrna&#x2019; (&#x39C;. &#x3A3;&#x3BC;&#x3C5;&#x3C1;&#x3BD;&#x3B1;&#x1FD6;&#x3BF;&#x3C2;) the poem 9,390 (with a pathos-filled description of an infanticide). 
      To which M. Meleager is referring is impossible to say: the frequency of the name speaks against identification, which would assume a
      corruption in the ethnika."  Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna).  "Menecrates." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and ; 
      Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2011. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 28 January 2011 </mads:note>
